[]: After Unit-01 gained the S2 Engine... &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Quote Post by Replicator &raquo; Tue Dec 04, 2012 5:18 pm ...Could it have started walking freely without a pilot? Yui Ikari&#39;s soul is inside its core, and now Unit-01 has an S2 Engine, which would technically place it on the same level as an Angel. Or for the matter any S2 Engine-equipped EVA would fall under this category. Unit-04 before its demise, and the MP EVAs. Would those Units at least in theory, be able to operate autonomously without pilots or Dummy Plugs?

[]: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Quote Post by Reichu &raquo; Tue Dec 04, 2012 6:07 pm Precisely what binds Evas to the Lilin&#39;s will, beyond obvious things like &quot;power limits&quot;, has always been a bit steeped in vagueness. The central nervous system is subject to tampering, such that an entry plug with pilot &quot;completes the circuit&quot;. This measure has apparently been foolproof enough to thwart even Angels &#40;Bardiel couldn&#39;t take over Eva-03 until the entry plug with Toji was present&#41;, but hasn&#39;t worked as completely on the Evas themselves &#40;Yui is capable of at least some movement when she has zero power and a signal terminator inserted in her spine&#41;. At any rate, my overall impression is that it takes more than an S2 Engine to liberate an Eva, otherwise the MP Evas wouldn&#39;t have made such wonderful slaves. My assumption has been that, after getting the S2 Engine, Eva-01 / Yui only retains her cybernetic implants because she will need them to make Shinji the focal point of Third Impact and HIP later. If she had really wanted to, she could have regenerated all of that mechanical crap away. &#40;Then, this doesn&#39;t explain why she&#39;s still maintaining her implants when she&#39;s however many lightyears away from Earth and not likely to ever use them again...&#41;

